How customer reviews and ratings work

Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

NunyaBizNiss
5.0 out of 5 stars We are enormous fans of this franchise and have been so sad its been gone for so long
Reviewed in the United States on October 28, 2015
Platform For Display: PlayStation 4Edition: 2-Pack BundleVerified Purchase
FULL DISCLOSURE: We are enormous fans of this franchise and have been so sad its been gone for so long, so this review may be a little bias but if you like Guitar hero, you should just go get this. If you need to be sold on it, keep reading. So, just got Guitar Hero Live for PS4 with two Guitar Controllers. The button layout is way better and more fun in my opinion. You dont have to rely on that gimpy pinky finger, you get to use your strong fingers and its more challenging because there are more combos, while still being more fun. The game play is; you on a stage, with the band. Its super intuitive and if you start sucking, everyone starts reacting accordingly and when you nail it, its very seamless in the A.I. and how the live actors transition between "Yeah you rock!" to "Dude, whats wrong with you!?". The entire crowd is the same and some of the hot girls in bikinis are distracting, but pleasantly so. It has plenty of douchey dudes for the ladies in your party to ogle as well. Nothing is inappropriate in my opinion so you can enjoy with your kids friends parents after a couple beers...This one is fun, hands down. If you're some cynical little teenage crap, you may not like it. If you're into good music, good fun with your family and friends, acting silly playing this, then buy this and enjoy.

UPDATE: Ok this review was pre GHTV experience. So GHTV is gonna wreck my life its so addicting. I wont explain what it is, there are plenty of sites who have done that. All I can say is, they really got this right. My ONLY gripe is there is currently no Tool songs AND I would like GH to release the old versions for DLC (World Tour was epic, we want it back!)

Dionys Heredia
5.0 out of 5 stars Great Vicious Game
Reviewed in the United States on February 8, 2016
Platform For Display: PlayStation 4Edition: 2-Pack BundleVerified Purchase
Guitar Hero Live 2-Pack Bundle - PlayStation 4

This is by far the best GH Game I've played. It has real crowd reaction that cheers you up when you're rocking and boo you when you're being sloppy. The new mechanics of the game is way different than it used to be. Now it has two lines of 3 buttons; black and white. This can make you feel like your actually playing a real guitar and if you're not used to move your fingers like a guitarist you will have get used to it FAST because to be honest, who plays GH in normal speed?

It's divided in two separate experiences. Guitar Hero Live: lets you player the single player of the game and Guitar Hero TV allows you to go online and choose what songs you want to play at a cost of Game plays, you can either pay money to get plays to choose one song in particular, o you can just play the Single player to get them, I've used most of the game content and haven't spent a single dime in it. It also have Music Channels where you can play the songs they play infinitely. you can also put down your guitar and the game will remove the Highway and act like a real music channel and listen to music whenever you have friends at home.

Overall is a very good game and will recommend it to anyone to like to play music and to be honest I'm not a very rock person but if you give me a guitar and music I'm definitely down for it.

It came with:

Two guitars with a 2 Two-Pack AA batteries

Jordan D. Leichtweis
1.0 out of 5 stars Ok game, but the guitars are way too unreliable
Reviewed in the United States on March 26, 2016
Platform For Display: PlayStation 4Edition: 2-Pack BundleVerified Purchase
The game is ok, but beware of the controllers. My wife and I don't really have that much time to play, but we both grew up playing video games, so I decided to buy this since there are not that many 2-player games available on the ps4. The game was ok, but after playing it a few times, the buttons started sticking. Unfortunately, since my wife and I don't get that many opportunities to play video games that often, we didn't realize the buttons were sticking until after a few months. Now we cannot return or exchange the guitars. We just have 2 guitars and a game collecting dust. I wouldn't waste your money on this game. There is a reason why guitar hero and rock band are going extinct. The games may be fun, but the controllers for these games are too unreliable. This isn't the first guitar hero that I have purchased that had a problem with the guitar.
